The teachers welcomed us in with open arms, and it was a moment of pride as Carter and Dev got to share something unique about our Indian culture and family traditions with their classmates. I’m sharing a FREE resource for you (head over to IG same handle!) with a detailed lesson plan and links to everything we used! At a time where many of us are losing our faith in humanity and feel a divide in our foundational beliefs of goodness over evil, this lesson felt appropriate and necessary. We have to keep doing the work to teach inclusivity and acceptance. It takes all of us.❤️ Peep the 🪔pajamas at the end!

Beamer reported that one passenger had been killed and that a flight attendant had told him that both the pilot and co-pilot had been forced from the cockpit and may have been injured. He was also on the phone when the plane made a quick and violent turn. Later, he told the operator that he and some of the other passengers were planning to attack the hijackers and regain control of the aircraft, after they learned about what happened at the World Trade Center and The Pentagon. According to Jefferson, Beamer’s last audible words were “Are you ready? Okay. Let’s roll.”⁠ •⁠ The bravery demonstrated on this day is hard to comprehend. And we’ll never know how many people the small group of passengers on Flight 93 actually saved. Todd was among many others who showed terrific bravery on this terrible day in US history. Replying to @mkeydeez Sam Norton was described to me as a “fiercely loyal” and “the kind of friend you would always want in your corner because it meant you would be safe and cared for.” He took up running a few years ago and became devoted. He formed the Almost Friday Run Club and built a great community of fellow runners.  Tragically, Sam collapsed and lost his life on the 23rd mile of the Santa Rosa marathon this past August. Him and his friends had intended on crushing the Santa Rosa Marathon and doing their “victory lap” at the NYC marathon.  The rest is a direct quote from Sam’s friend, who is in the video and messaged me about his friend: “After that day, I really didn’t want to be a part of the race yesterday. I genuinely couldn’t imagine being out there without him. But his mom had asked us to take over Sam's bib (he was planning to run through the Herren Project, a cause that was deeply personal and meaningful to Sam as he lost his father in 2020 to substance abuse disorder in 2020).  While we agreed to run it for Sam, we wanted to turn it into a way we could honor and celebrate Sam. We coordinated with NYRR to get us a SAM bib and that was one of Sam’s favorite shirts, which we imagined he’d wear on raceday. All the signatures on the Bib are family and friends along the route, and the two of us ran with Sam from mile 23 onward to finish what he started.

I spent 2 hours walking around in the blazing sun. It was my cousin’s birthday and she decided to go out for breakfast with a group of girls to get açaí bowls. I ate a breakfast protein bowl and an açaí bowl. I was the only one to get a meal with my açaí bowl, but even though I had two things to eat…I was still hungry. They all decided to walk around a bit and chat. After two hours of that…I was sweating, thirsty and hungry. So me and my mom decided to leave and go grocery shopping at Trader Joe’s. After grabbing what we needed, we both decided to go out and eat. As we were driving looking around, we came upon an Olive Garden. My mom reminds me of the stuffed pasta shells they have, and I immediately craved them. So we went and got a booth and looked over the menu. “Stuffed shells” were nowhere to be seen on the menu. My heart broke. I was excited over nothing. The waitress came up to see if we were ready to order (for some reason she gave off the weirdest vibe ever. idk if I was tripping) my mom asked her if they have stuffed shells. She said yes. I was throbbing in excitement. The waitress asked me what sauce I wanted. I got confused. Doesn’t it always come with marinara? Maybe they give options now so I just stuck with marinara.  “Do you wanna add a protein to it?”  This is where I was like woah. This dish just keeps getting better.  “You can do that?” I asked in pure confusion. She nodded her head so I asked for crispy chicken. She takes my mom’s order and walks away. I spend the next 10-15 minutes munching on breadsticks and salad just picturing how this meal is gonna come out. I wonder how will they plate this magnificent meal? I never had stuffed shells with all these accommodations. I was genuinely excited. I see the waitress coming to our table with a tray. Oh boy! My yummy special dish is coming! She sets the plate in front of me.  erm… it was nothing that I was expecting. She misunderstood and gave me shell shaped pasta with marinara and chicken. My high went to an all time low. Why on earth would I order this? No wonder why she was asking me what sauce and protein I wanted. Imagine if I said “just how it is☺️” when she asked me if I wanted to add anything. She would have brought out plain pasta.  However, no matter how bummed out I was when my dish came I did not speak up about it. My mom insisted, but I declined cause I just cannot physically say anything or inconvenience someone (even if it is not a big deal for them at all). I nibbled on my meal and took the rest to go. I blamed me not wanting to speak up on the waitress’s weird vibe I got, but deep down I’m just very socially awkward.  I just want stuffed shells. Someone let me know if they still have it, #stuffedshells #fyp #socialanxiety #olivegarden #foryou

I cried in the testing center parking lot for 30 mins. No lie. Talk about a silent car ride home.. oh it was SILENT😂. Then, I found out most programs didn’t accept 2 of my science credits so that limited the number of programs I could apply to. I could literally only apply to 1 place and I didn’t get in. That just about sent me over the edge🥴. I retook 2 important chemistries my senior year of college and it almost broke me, but I didn’t give up.  I worked 2 jobs simultaneously to double my experience and was taking 17 credit hours when I really only had to take 13 my senior year. Most days I cried to my mom &  mentors.. but I didn’t quit. I never lost sight of the goal.  So this acceptance is VERYYYYY personal and deserving for me. It still feels surreal for me honestly, but I’m grateful that it’s finally happening. I KNOW the real work starts now, but I’m still enjoying my moment 🩺🫶🏾.  #acceprance #paschool #paschooljourney #gradschool

Designed according to ancient Hindu scriptures, the temple incorporates design elements from ancient Indian culture. It is the second largest Hindu temple in the world after Angkor Wat in Cambodia, which is spread over 500 acres.  Nearly two million cubic feet of stone was used in the construction of the Swaminarayan Akshardham, sourced from different sites around the world, including Turkey, Italy, India, and China. The Brahma Kund, a traditional Indian stepwell, contains water from over 300 bodies of water from around the world, including the holy rivers of India and all 50 states of the US. NO preclinical grades, no class rank, no shelf exams for clinicals and only P/F for clerkships, annonymous exams, we get up to 12 weeks of study time for the boards, tuition free optional 5th year for extra time to do research, other degrees and/or study for boards, collaborative students because no competition, great faculty to student ratio. I was the only Nay on the Ohio House Resolution on Israel. It was not an easy decision to make. No one wants to vote against a resolution condemning violence. But this resolution fell short of what it should have been. To condemn terror but to not ignore the damage and destruction endured by the Palestinian people.  I could not vote ‘Yes’ and abandon my Palestinian friends and neighbors who for too long had very few stand for them.  I still strongly pray for the Jewish lives lost and mourn with my Jewish friends and neighbors as they live through this devastating moment.   But as my friend Rep Isaacsohn stated: It is not moral equivalence to mourn the loss of all innocent lives including those in Gaza.  I cannot in good conscience sit here and vote yes on a resolution that does not ask for a de-escalation of violent retribution launched by Israel against largely civilian territory. The Palestinian children also deserve someone to stand up for them and condemn their murder. Those babies who right now are denied water, electricity and medicine, deserve to have someone stand up for them and condemn their abuse. An abuse they have suffered for over 75 years. With over 6,000 palestinian lives lost since 2008 and thousands more injured and displaced It is time to call for true justice and apply the values of universal human rights to all victims of oppression, regardless of nationality, religion or skin color.  I send my prayers for peace and the protection of innocent lives lost during this conflict. Be it Palestinian, Jewish, American or any other loss of life.  Israeli writer Gideon Levy stated: “We now have to cry bitterly for the Israeli victims, but we should also cry for Gaza" And finally to quote my favorite verse in the Quran: “O you who believe, be upholders of justice - witnesses for God, even though against (the interest of) yourselves or your parents, and kinsmen.” 4:135 #freepalestine

video_description: I saw my final 7th world wonder and I might’ve cried a little 🥹 If I’ve learned anything in life, it’s to go after the things that make you feel alive & set your soul on fire. And don’t stop until you’ve had enough! ❤️‍🔥 I remember graduating college and everyone telling me how proud they were and what an accomplishment it was.  But on the inside, I felt so normal. I thought ‘wow, this is anticlimactic’. So I started to travel because that was the only thing I truly wanted to do & could imagine myself doing as a new graduate 🗺️ & it changed my life. I stopped living for other people or for what was expected of me and I started living for MYSELF ✨ Flying in a helicopter over such a beautiful part of the world while getting to check off the last wonder on my list, left me feeling an immense gratitude and happiness for the life that I’ve created. More than graduating college ever did.  I read somewhere that only less than 5% of the population ever gets to see all 7 New World Wonders so I’m feeling extra special about this 🥹 So follow your dreams, guys 🫶🏼 there’s no better feeling than accomplishing them!  #7worldwonders #finalworldwonder #sevenwondersoftheworld #christtheredeemer

video_description: Here's a couple of the many things you could do, rather than scrolling through SHEIN or Amazon, or making that late night Walmart and Mcdonald's run if you're trying to save money! I hope you enjoy this <3 1. Take a Nap. This is probably the easiest, most simple thing you could do. It makes time pass by so much more quickly so you don't get those constant intrusive thoughts that'll cost you $20! Plus, if you've got a history of a bad sleep schedule this would be your opportunity to grab a couple more hours of sleep. 2. Try Yoga. I personally have just started practicing yoga and I feel like it helps me a lot. I get to wind down, calm my mind, and stretch my body out. I don't know about you, but I sleep in some funky positions that leave me cramped up. So doing a few stretches throughout the days really helps with those cramps and is a great alternative to working out (which I hate to do!!). 3. Try a New Recipe. Baking is one of my favorite things to do with friends. You don't even have to do any of these alone! If you have the basic necessities, you could bake or cook a lot of things at home. Try that frozen chocolate strawberry recipe off TikTok. Or if you're brave enough, try a professional chef tutorial on YouTube just for fun! 4. Clean Up Your Nails. I'm very picky about keeping my nails pretty and clean so it prevents me from wanting to pick at them as an old habit. You can paint your nails a pretty color, or just simply file them down a bit and clean up your cuticles. If you're a perfectionist like me, this will keep you occupied for quite some time. 5. Organize. I have a few drawers in my bedroom that I tend to just throw the most random things into, so I like to go through it every once and a while and I find some pretty crazy things. Clean up your desk, go through your bookshelf, or organize your clothes. Whatever you've been putting off, try it now. 6. Teach A Pet A Trick. Grab some treats and show your dog how to roll over, dance in a circle, or give a high five. If you're a cat person, there's a way to teach your cat how to give you a high five :) 7. Watch Something. Find a documentary on Netflix that's trending, or ask a friend for a movie recommendation. I have about 5 different tv shows I'm in the middle of watching, so if you have that habit then make it a goal to finish one of them! 8. Dance!! This is a great opportunity to just let yourself lose and calm down, and even find a few new songs that pique your interests. Turn on some 2000s party songs and dance around your room while you get a couple side tasks done! #lemon8diary #savemoney #thingstodo #bored #funwithfriends #lemon8us #lemon8 Follow @mariahnichole0 on Lemon8 for more!

I didn't wake up in the hospital thinking I was invincible and was gonna get back to surfing. Now I get to surf with my two eldest sons Tobias and Wesley and my hubby! I get to enjoy these sweet moments with my newborn daughter. There is so much to be grateful for, and these past 20 years have been filled with incredible moments and huge overcoming seasons. When you have your “Shark Attack” moments in life.
